 the dose side effects other than those listed here may also occur talk to your doctor about any side effect that seems unusual or that is especially bothersome you can also call the doctors office and ask to speak to him and go over your questions or you could try calling the pharmacy and talk to the pharmacist they should be able to help you get answers as well good luck Traumatic brain injury Doxepin Maprotiline Chlorpromazine Psoriasis Prostate cancer Narcotic Trazodone Analgesic Clinical depression Cephalexin Buprenorphine Hypoglycemia Sulfasalazine Urinary incontinence Hydrocodone Oxycodone Paracetamol Cancer Hyperthermia Paroxetine Allergy Myocardial infarction Drug addiction Topiramate Radiation therapy Dehydration Pneumonia Haloperidol Sleep Asthma Hay fever Pethidine Aspartame Insulin Electroconvulsive therapy Addiction Chronic fatigue syndrome Epilepsy Ebola Diabetes mellitus Methamphetamine First aid Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Obstetrics Propranolol Multiple chemical sensitivity Decompression sickness Panic attack Migraine Breastfeeding Osteoarthritis Stroke Drowning Multiple sclerosis Group A streptococcal infection Medical cannabis Fecal incontinence Antihistamine Charles Darwin's illness Antidepressant Sleep apnea Anxiety LSD Common cold Trimipramine Folic acid Caffeine Herpes simplex virus Tobacco smoking Porphyria Tricyclic antidepressant Bipolar disorder Cephalic disorder Antipsychotic Cocaine Stuttering Cannabis (drug) Balance disorder Intracranial pressure Venlafaxine Chemotherapy M__ni__re___s disease Clozapine Medicine Parkinson's disease Citalopram Tianeptine Gastroparesis Vigabatrin 